Great speaking with you! As mentioned, your submission is pending 2 former manager references from an end client (name, phone number, company). Once I have those, I will submit your profile to this AI Engineer role for 3 months + extensions, hybrid 2-3 days per week on site in Menlo Park, CA, at $80 per hour w2 all inc.

Location: 2-3 days ONSITE Hybrid - Menlo Park, California 94025<https://maps.app.goo.gl/qozvFVLfUF2xp5ss6>
Start Date: ASAP (mid Feb)
Duration: 3 months plus extensions


AI Engineer
The client is a low-code software development company that enables organizations to rapidly build, deploy, and manage enterprise-grade web and mobile applications. Its platform combines visual development with extensibility for custom code, allowing teams to accelerate delivery while still supporting complex, scalable, and secure solutions. The client is commonly used by IT and digital transformation teams to modernize legacy systems, integrate with cloud and enterprise platforms, and respond quickly to evolving business needs.

Project:
The client is in the early stages of building new AI-driven capabilities and is seeking an experienced AI Engineer Consultant to help design, build, and deploy AI agents and intelligent data solutions. This role will be hands-on and highly technical, supporting the development of AI products focused on financial services and insurance use cases, including risk prediction, analytics, and decision automation. The ideal candidate brings a strong background in banking or insurance environments and has previously built and operationalized AI agents and machine-learning–driven products within regulated financial systems.

The role requires a strong understanding of AI engineering principles, model lifecycle management, and AI system architecture, with a focus on risk modeling, predictive analytics, and explainable AI in regulated environments. The consultant will also help translate business and risk requirements into scalable AI solutions and ensure models align with risk standards common in financial institutions.
Required Skills:

* Strong background as a Data Engineer with hands on experience building AI agents and AI-driven products
* Proven experience working in banking, financial services, or insurance environments
* Hands on experience with machine learning models, data science modeling, and predictive analytics
* Experience building and deploying AI/ML solutions focused on financial risk, insurance risk, or decision intelligence
* Strong data engineering skills, including data pipeline development, data modeling, and working with large, complex datasets
* Ability to write, transform, and analyze data to support AI and ML use cases
* Deep understanding of financial and insurance domain concepts, including risk, compliance, and regulatory considerations
* Experience taking AI models from concept through production in enterprise environments


Best Regards,
Tori Enis | Data & Artificial Intelligence Rec
